- @title = 'Tabbing between Ajax pages'

#summary
  :textile
    h2. Creating simple image galleries with @Ojay.ImageTabs@
    
    Turning a list of linked thumbnails into a simple image gallery is a very common pattern.
    Here we demonstrate how to do this with the @Ojay.ImageTabs@ class. The image for each
    tab is not loaded until the first time that tab is selected, reducing the initial load
    time for a page using this component.

:plain
    <style id="display-style" type="text/css">
        #thumbnails {
            float:         left;
            margin:        0 0 40px 24px;
        }
        
        #thumbnails li {
            margin:        0 0 8px 0;
            padding:       0;
            list-style:    none;
        }
        
        #thumbnails li a, #thumbnails li a img {
            display:       block;
            margin:        0;
            border:        none;
            padding:       0;
            outline:       none;
        }
        
        #thumbnails li a {
            border:        4px solid #e5e5e5;
        }
        
        #thumbnails .selected {
            border-color:  #c7d900;
        }
        
        #image-container {
            float:         left;
            width:         192px;
            height:        192px;
            margin:        40px;
        }
        
        #image-container img {
            border:        4px solid #e5e5e5;
        }
    </style>
    
    <ul id="thumbnails">
        <li><a href="/images/tabs/godel.jpg"><img alt="Kurt GÃ¶del" src="/images/tabs/godel_thumb.jpg" /></a></li>
        <li><a href="/images/tabs/escher.jpg"><img alt="M.C. Escher" src="/images/tabs/escher_thumb.jpg" /></a></li>
        <li><a href="/images/tabs/bach.jpg"><img alt="J.S. Bach" src="/images/tabs/bach_thumb.jpg" /></a></li>
    </ul>
    
    <script id="display-script" type="text/javascript">
        var list = Ojay('#thumbnails'), links = list.descendants('a');
        
        var holder = Ojay(Ojay.HTML.div({id: 'image-container'}));
        list.insert(holder, 'after');
        
        var tabs = Ojay.ImageTabs.fromLinks(links, holder);
        tabs.setup();
    </script>
